name: Alwaleed bin Talal
bio: Al-Waleed Bin Talal bin Abdulaziz al Saud is a Saudi business magnate, investor, and philanthropist. He is a member of the Saudi royal family.

name: Brit Hume
bio: Alexander Britton "Brit" Hume is an American television journalist and political commentator.Hume had a 23-year career with ABC News, where he contributed to World News Tonight with Peter Jennings, Nightline and This Week.

name: Alisyn Camerota
bio: Alisyn Lane Camerota is an American television news journalist who is co-anchoring CNN's New Day. She has co-anchored CNN Tonight, and served in many roles during a 16-year career at the Fox News Channel.

name: Amy Chozick
bio: Amy Chozick is an American political reporter who works for the New York Times and primarily writes about Hillary Clinton and her family.

name: Ana Navarro
bio: Ana Navarro Flores is a Nicaraguan-born American Republican strategist and political commentator for various news outlets, including CNN, CNN en EspaÌ±ol, ABC News, Telemundo, and The View.

name: Anderson Cooper
bio: Anderson Hays Cooper is an American author and television personality. He is the primary anchor of the CNN news show Anderson Cooper 360.

name: Angela Merkel
bio: Angela Dorothea Merkel is a German stateswoman and former research scientist. Merkel has been the Chancellor of Germany since 2005, and the leader of the Christian Democratic Union since 2000.

name: Anthony D. Weiner
bio: Anthony David Weiner is an American politician and former Congressman who served New York's 9th congressional district from January 1999 until June 2011. A member of the Democratic Party, he won seven terms, never receiving less than 59% of the vote.

name: Arianna Huffington
bio: Arianna Huffington is a Greek American author, syndicated columnist, occasional actress, and businesswoman.Huffington is the co-founder and editor-in-chief of The Huffington Post, which is now owned by AOL.

name: Bakari Sellers
bio: Bakari T. Sellers is an American politician and attorney. He represented South Carolina's 90th district in the lower house of the state legislature from 2006 to 2014.

name: Barack Obama
bio: Barack Hussein Obama II is an American politician who is the 44th and current President of the United States. He is the first African American to hold the office and the first president born outside the continental United States.

name: Ben Sasse
bio: Benjamin Eric "Ben" Sasse is an American politician. Sasse, a member of the Republican Party, is the junior United States Senator from the state of Nebraska.

name: Ben Cardin
bio: Benjamin Louis "Ben" Cardin is an American politician and member of the Democratic Party who serves as the junior United States Senator from Maryland, in office since 2007.

name: Ben Carson
bio: Benjamin Solomon "Ben" Carson, Sr. is an American retired neurosurgeon. Born in Detroit, Michigan, and a graduate of Yale University and the University of Michigan Medical School, Carson has authored numerous books on his medical career and political stances, and was the subject of a television drama film in 2009.

name: Bernie Sanders
bio: Bernard "Bernie" Sanders is an American politician, serving as the junior United States Senator from Vermont since 2007. Sanders is the longest-serving independent in U.S. congressional history.

name: Bernard Goldberg
bio: Bernard Richard Goldberg, also known as Bernie Goldberg, is an American writer, journalist, and political pundit. Goldberg has won twelve Emmy Awards during his career.

name: Bill de Blasio
bio: Bill de Blasio is an American politician who is serving as the 109th mayor of New York City. From 2010 to 2013, he held the citywide office of New York City public advocate, serving as an ombudsman between the electorate and the city government.

name: Carly Fiorina
bio: Cara Carleton "Carly" Fiorina is an American businesswoman. Fiorina is known primarily for her tenure as the Chief Executive Officer of Hewlett-Packard.

name: Carl Cameron
bio: Carl Cameron is an American television journalist and commentator for Fox News Channel.

name: Whoopi Goldberg
bio: Caryn Elaine Johnson, known professionally by her stage name, Whoopi Goldberg, is an American actress, comedian, and television host.

name: Chuck Todd
bio: Charles David "Chuck" Todd is an American television journalist who is the 12th moderator of Meet the Press, and host of Meet the Press Daily on MSNBC. He also serves as the Political Director for NBC News.

name: Charles Koch
bio: Charles de Ganahl Koch is an American businessman, political donor and philanthropist. He is co-owner, chairman of the board, and chief executive officer of Koch Industries, while his brother David H. Koch serves as Executive Vice President. Charles and David each own 42% of the conglomerate.

name: Joe Scarborough
bio: Charles Joseph "Joe" Scarborough is an American cable news and talk radio host, lawyer, author, and former politician. He is currently the co-host of Morning Joe on MSNBC, and previously hosted Scarborough Country on the same channel.

name: Charles Krauthammer
bio: Charles Krauthammer is an American syndicated columnist, author, political commentator, and non-practicing physician whose weekly column is syndicated to more than 400 publications worldwide.

name: Charles Lane
bio: Charles Lane was an American character actor whose career spanned 64 years. Lane gave his last performance at the age of 90. Lane appeared in many Frank Capra films, including You Can't Take It With You, Mr.

name: Charles Blow
bio: Charles McRay Blow is an American journalist, liberal commentator, and the current visual op-ed columnist for The New York Times.

name: Cheri Jacobus
bio: Cheri Jacobus is a conservative political strategist, pundit and writer. A frequent guest on CNN, MSNBC, FOX News and CBS.com, she has been an adjunct professor at George Washington University's graduate school of political management since 2007, and a political columnist at The Hill newspaper since February 2009.

name: Chris Christie
bio: Christopher James "Chris" Christie is an American attorney, politician and member of the Republican Party who has been the 55th Governor of New Jersey since January 2010. His term ends January 16, 2018.

name: Colin Powell
bio: Colin Luther Powell is an American statesman and a retired four-star general in the United States Army. He was the 65th United States Secretary of State, serving under U.S. President George W. Bush from 2001 to 2005, the first African American to serve in that position.

name: Cory Booker
bio: Cory Anthony Booker is an American politician and the junior United States Senator from New Jersey, in office since 2013. Previously he served as mayor of Newark from 2006 to 2013.

name: Dana Perino
bio: Dana Marie Perino is an American political commentator and author. She was the 27th White House Press Secretary, serving under President George W. Bush from September 14, 2007 to January 20, 2009.

name: Dan Henninger
bio: Daniel Henninger is an American journalist. He serves as the Deputy Editorial Page Director of The Wall Street Journal and a Fox News contributor.

name: David Brooks
bio: David Brooks is an American conservative political and cultural commentator who writes for The New York Times. He has worked as a reporter and later op-ed editor for The Wall Street Journal; a senior editor at The Weekly Standard from its inception; a contributing editor at Newsweek and The Atlantic Monthly; and as a commentator on NPR.

name: David Gregory
bio: David Michael Gregory is an American television journalist and the former moderator of NBC News' Sunday morning talk show Meet the Press. Gregory currently serves as CNN political analyst, since 2016.

name: Shep Smith
bio: David Shepard Smith Jr., known better as Shepard Smith or Shep Smith, is an American television news anchor. He is the former host of Fox Report with Shepard Smith and Studio B weekdays on Fox News Channel.

name: Debbie Wasserman Schultz
bio: Deborah "Debbie" Wasserman Schultz is an American politician. She is the U.S. Representative for Florida's 23rd congressional district, a member of the Democratic Party who served as chairperson of the Democratic National Committee from 2011 to 2016.

name: Don Lemon
bio: Don Lemon is an American television personality. He is based in New York City and currently hosts CNN Tonight.

name: Donny Deutsch
bio: Donald Jay "Donny" Deutsch is an American advertising executive and television personality.He is the former host of the CNBC talk show The Big Idea with Donny Deutsch.

name: Graydon Carter
bio: Edward Graydon Carter is a Canadian-born American journalist and has served as the editor of Vanity Fair since 1992. He also co-founded, with Kurt Andersen and Tom Phillips, the satirical monthly magazine Spy in 1986.

name: Elizabeth Warren
bio: Elizabeth Ann Warren is an American academic and politician. She is a member of the Democratic Party, and is the senior United States Senator from Massachusetts.

name: Elizabeth Beck
bio: Elizabeth Beck is a founder and managing partner of Beck & Lee law firm. She is a graduate of the University of California Los Angeles and Yale Law School.

name: Erick Erickson
bio: Erick Erickson is a politically conservative American blogger who hosts radio show Atlanta's Evening News with Erick Erickson, broadcast on 750 WSB.

name: Errol Louis
bio: Errol Louis is a New York City journalist and television show host.Louis is the current host of Inside City Hall, a program about New York City politics that airs nightly on NY1.

name: Frank Bruni
bio: Frank Anthony Bruni is an American journalist. He was the chief restaurant critic of the New York Times, from 2004 to 2009. In June 2011, he was named an Op-ed columnist for the newspaper, its first openly gay one.

name: Frank Luntz
bio: Frank I. Luntz is an American political consultant, pollster, and "public opinion guru" best known for developing talking points and other messaging for various Republican causes.

name: George Pataki
bio: George Elmer Pataki is an American lawyer and politician who served as the 53rd Governor of New York. A member of the Republican Party, Pataki was a lawyer who was elected Mayor of his home town of Peekskill, later going on to be elected to State Assembly, then State Senate.

name: George Will
bio: George Frederick Will is a Pulitzer Prize winning conservative political commentator. In 1986, The Wall Street Journal called him "perhaps the most powerful journalist in America", in a league with Walter Lippmann.

name: George H.W. Bush
bio: George Herbert Walker Bush is an American politician who was the 41st President of the United States from 1989 to 1993 and the 43rd Vice President of the United States from 1981 to 1989. A member of the U.S.

name: George W. Bush
bio: George Walker Bush is an American politician who was the 43rd President of the United States from 2001 to 2009 and 46th Governor of Texas from 1995 to 2000. The eldest son of Barbara and George H. W. Bush, he was born in New Haven, Connecticut.

name: Glenn Beck
bio: Glenn Lee Beck is an American television and radio host, conservative political commentator, author, television network producer, filmmaker, and entrepreneur.

name: Gonzalo P. Curiel
bio: Gonzalo Paul Curiel is a United States District Judge for the United States District Court for the Southern District of California.

name: Hallie Jackson
bio: Hallie Marie Jackson is a correspondent for NBC News and an anchor for its cable division, MSNBC. She has worked in Salisbury, Maryland; Dover, Delaware; Hartford, Connecticut; New Haven, Connecticut; and Baltimore, Maryland before joining NBC News in 2014.

name: Harry Hurt III
bio: Harry Hurt III is an award winning print journalist, a video journalist, and the author of six non-fiction books. He wrote 98 consecutive Executive Pursuits columns and made 14 related web videos for the Saturday business section of the New York Times starting in May 2005 and ending in February 2009.

name: Hillary Clinton
bio: Hillary Diane Rodham Clinton is an American politician and the Democratic Party nominee for President of the United States in the 2016 election.

name: Hugh Hewitt
bio: Hugh Hewitt is an American radio talk show host with the Salem Radio Network and a lawyer, academic, and author. A conservative and a Catholic, he comments on society, politics, and media bias in the United States.

name: Huma Abedin
bio: Huma Mahmood Abedin is an American political staffer who serves as vice chairwoman of Hillary Clinton's 2016 campaign for President. Prior to that, she served as the deputy chief of staff to U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton from 2009 to 2013.

name: Rick Perry
bio: James Richard "Rick" Perry is an American politician who served as the 47th Governor of Texas from December 2000 to January 2015.

name: Jeff Zucker
bio: Jeffrey Adam "Jeff" Zucker is the current president of CNN Worldwide. He previously served as the President and CEO of NBC Universal. Zucker has also served as an Executive in Residence at Columbia Business School.

name: Jeff Flake
bio: Jeffry Lane "Jeff" Flake is an American politician and member of the Republican Party who has served as the Junior United States Senator from Arizona since 2013.

name: Jennifer Rubin
bio: Jennifer Rubin is an American conservative journalist. She writes the "Right Turn" blog for The Washington Post. Previously she worked at Commentary, PJ Media, Human Events, and The Weekly Standard.

name: Jeb Bush
bio: John Ellis "Jeb" Bush, Sr. is an American businessman and politician who served as the 43rd Governor of Florida from 1999 to 2007.Bush, who grew up in Houston, is the second son of former President George H. W. Bush and former First Lady Barbara Bush, and a younger brother of former President George W. Bush.

name: John Roberts
bio: John Glover Roberts Jr. is the 17th and current Chief Justice of the United States. He took his seat on September 29, 2005, having been nominated by President George W. Bush after the death of Chief Justice William Rehnquist.

name: John Harwood
bio: John Harwood is an American journalist who is the chief Washington Correspondent for CNBC. He is also a contributor for The New York Times. He writes a weekly column entitled "The Caucus" that appears on Monday about Washington politics and policy. Before joining the Times, he wrote for The Wall Street Journal.

name: John Sununu
bio: John Henry Sununu is a Cuban-born American politician. He served as the 75th Governor of New Hampshire and later White House Chief of Staff under President George H. W. Bush. He is the father of John E. Sununu, the former United States Senator from New Hampshire, and Christopher Sununu. Sununu was the chairman of the New Hampshire Republican Party from 2009 to 2011.

name: John Legere
bio: John J. Legere is an American businessman who is the chief executive officer and president of T-Mobile US. He previously served as an executive for AT&T, Dell, Global Crossing, and serves on the CTIA board of directors.

name: John R. Allen
bio: John R. Allen is a retired United States Marine Corps four-star general, and past Deputy Commander of U.S. Central Command, prior to serving as Commander of the International Security Assistance Force and U.S. Forces Afghanistan.

name: John Kasich
bio: John Richard Kasich is an American politician, the 69th and current Governor of Ohio, first elected in 2010 and re-elected in 2014. He is a member of the Republican Party.

name: John McCain
bio: John Sidney McCain III is the senior United States Senator from Arizona and the Republican presidential nominee for the 2008 United States presidential election.

name: John Oliver
bio: John William Oliver is an English comedian, political commentator, television host, and occasional actor. He is the host of HBO's Peabody Award-winning late-night talk Last Week Tonight with John Oliver.

name: Jonathan Martin
bio: Jonathan August Martin is a former American football offensive tackle. He was drafted by the Miami Dolphins in the second round of the 2012 NFL Draft and has also played for the San Francisco 49ers. He played college football at Stanford.

name: Joe Biden
bio: Joseph Robinette "Joe" Biden Jr. is the 47th and current Vice President of the United States, having been jointly elected twice with President Barack Obama.

name: Joy Behar
bio: Joy Behar is an American comedian, writer, actress, and a co-host on the ABC daytime talk show The View. She hosted The Joy Behar Show on HLN from 2009 to 2011 and Joy Behar: Say Anything!

name: Juan Williams
bio: Juan Antonio Williams is a Panamanian-born American journalist and political analyst for Fox News Channel. He also writes for several newspapers including The Washington Post, The New York Times, and The Wall Street Journal and has been published in magazines such as The Atlantic Monthly and Time.

name: Karl Rove
bio: Karl Christian Rove is an American Republican political consultant and policy advisor. He was Senior Advisor and Deputy Chief of Staff during the George W. Bush administration until Rove's resignation on August 31, 2007.

name: Kasie Hunt
bio: Kasie S. Hunt is an American political correspondent for NBC News and MSNBC.

name: Katy Tur
bio: Katharine Bear "Katy" Tur is an American broadcast journalist working for NBC News. Tur is an NBC News correspondent based in New York City.

name: Katie Couric
bio: Katherine Anne "Katie" Couric is an American journalist and author. She currently serves as Yahoo! Global News Anchor. Couric has been a television host on all Big Three television networks in the United States.

name: Lawrence O'Donnell
bio: Lawrence Francis O'Donnell, Jr. is an American political analyst, journalist, actor, producer, writer, and host of The Last Word with Lawrence O'Donnell, a Monday through Thursday evening MSNBC opinion and news program.

name: Brent Bozell
bio: Leo Brent Bozell III, is an American conservative writer and activist who founded the Media Research Center, the Conservative Communications Center, and the Cybercast News Service.

name: Lincoln Chafee
bio: Lincoln Davenport Chafee is an American politician from Rhode Island. He served as mayor of Warwick from 1993 to 1999, as a United States Senator from 1999 to 2007, and as the 74th Governor of Rhode Island from 2011 to 2015.

name: Lindsey Graham
bio: Lindsey Olin Graham is an American politician and member of the Republican Party, who has served as a United States Senator from South Carolina since 2003, and has been the senior Senator from South Carolina since 2005.

name: Maggie Haberman
bio: Maggie Lindsy Haberman is a reporter and writer for The New York Times, based in New York City and a political analyst for CNN.

name: Major Garrett
bio: Major Elliott Garrett is Chief White House Correspondent with CBS News and Correspondent at Large with National Journal. Prior to joining National Journal he was the senior White House correspondent for the Fox News Channel.

name: Marc Thiessen
bio: Marc Alexander Thiessen is an American author, columnist and political commentator. He served as a speechwriter for United States President George W. Bush and Secretary of Defense Donald Rumsfeld.

name: Marco Rubio
bio: Marco Antonio Rubio is an American politician and attorney, and the junior United States Senator from Florida. Rubio previously served as Speaker of the Florida House of Representatives.

name: Mark Cuban
bio: Mark Cuban is an American businessman and investor. He is the owner of the NBA's Dallas Mavericks, Landmark Theatres, and Magnolia Pictures, and is the chairman of the HDTV cable network AXS TV.

name: Mark Halperin
bio: Mark Evan Halperin is co-managing editor of Bloomberg Politics and a senior political analyst for MSNBC and Bloomberg Television. He is the co-author of Game Change and Double Down: Game Change 2012. Both Halperin and Heilemann are co-hosts of MSNBC and Bloomberg's With All Due Respect, a political analysis show.

name: Marty Walsh
bio: Martin Joseph "Marty" Walsh is an American politician from Boston, Massachusetts. A Democrat, he is the 54th and current Mayor of Boston, in office since 2014.

name: Martin O'Malley
bio: Martin Joseph O'Malley is an American politician who was the 61st Governor of Maryland from 2007 to 2015. He previously served as the Mayor of Baltimore from 1999 to 2007, and was a Baltimore City Councilor from 1991 to 1999.

name: Mary Katharine Ham
bio: Mary Katharine Ham is an American journalist. She is editor at large of Hot Air, a contributing editor to Townhall Magazine, senior writer at The Federalist and a CNN contributor. At CPAC 2014, she was presented with the ACU Blogger of the Year award. She was previously a Fox News Channel contributor for eight years.

name: Cokie Roberts
bio: Mary Martha Corinne Morrison Claiborne Roberts, best known as Cokie Roberts, is an American journalist and author. She is a reporter on contract to National Public Radio as well as a regular roundtable analyst for the current This Week With George Stephanopoulos.

name: Maureen Dowd
bio: Maureen Bridgid Dowd is an American columnist for The New York Times, and a best-selling author. During the 1970s and the early 1980s, Dowd worked for Time magazine and the Washington Star, where she covered news and sports and wrote feature articles.

name: Meghan McCain
bio: Meghan Marguerite McCain is an American columnist, author, FOX News Channel host and contributor, and blogger. She is the daughter of U.S. Senator John McCain and Cindy Hensley McCain.

name: Megyn Kelly
bio: Megyn Marie Kelly, formerly known as Megyn Kendall, is an American journalist, political commentator and former corporate defense attorney, on the Fox News Channel.

name: Michael Nutter
bio: Michael Anthony Nutter is an American politician who was the 98th Mayor of Philadelphia. Elected on November 6, 2007, he was reelected to a second term on November 8, 2011.

name: Michael Barbaro
bio: Michael Barbaro is a political reporter for the New York Times covering the 2016 campaign. He is the host of The Run-Up, NYT's twice-weekly election podcast.

name: Michael J. Morell
bio: Michael Joseph Morell is an American intelligence analyst. He served as the deputy director of the Central Intelligence Agency as well as its acting director twice, first in 2011 and then from 2012 to 2013.

name: Michael Bloomberg
bio: Michael Rubens "Mike" Bloomberg is an American business magnate, politician, and philanthropist.Bloomberg is the founder, CEO, and owner of Bloomberg L.P., the global financial data and media company that bears his name, and is notable for its Bloomberg Terminal, which is widely used by investment professionals around the world.

name: Mika Brzezinski
bio: Mika Emilie Leonia Brzezinski is an American television host, author and journalist. Brzezinski co-hosts MSNBC's weekday morning broadcast Morning Joe with former Republican representative Joe Scarborough.

name: Molly Sims
bio: Molly Sims is an American model and actress. She rose to prominence for her appearances in the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issues and her role as Delinda Deline in the NBC drama Las Vegas.

name: Mort Zuckerman
bio: Mortimer Benjamin "Mort" Zuckerman is a Canadian-born American media proprietor, magazine editor, and investor. He is the co-founder, executive chairman and former CEO of Boston Properties, one of the largest real estate investment trusts in the United States.

name: Neil Young
bio: Neil Percival Young, OC OM is a Canadian singer-songwriter and musician, producer, director and screenwriter. He began performing in a group covering Shadows instrumentals in Canada in 1960, before moving to California in 1966, where he co-founded the band Buffalo Springfield together with Stephen Stills and Richie Furay, and later joined Crosby, Stills & Nash in 1969.

name: Nicolle Wallace
bio: Nicolle Wallace is an American author, political commentator for NBC News, and chief political analyst for MSNBC. She served as communications chief during the presidency of George W. Bush and in his 2004 re-election campaign.

name: Nikki Haley
bio: Nikki Haley is an American politician who has served as the 116th Governor of South Carolina since 2011. Prior to becoming governor, she represented Lexington County in the South Carolina House of Representatives from 2005 to 2011.

name: Paul Begala
bio: Paul Edward Begala is an American political consultant and political commentator. He was an adviser to President Bill Clinton. Begala was a chief strategist for the 1992 ClintonGore campaign, which carried 33 states and made Clinton the first Democrat to win the White House in twelve years.

name: Paul Singer
bio: Paul Elliott Singer is an American hedge fund manager, activist investor, and philanthropist. His hedge fund, Elliott Management Corporation specializes in distressed debt acquisitions.

name: Paulina Vega
bio: Paulina Vega Dieppa is a Colombian actress, TV Host, model and beauty queen who was crowned Miss Colombia 2013 and Miss Universe 2014.

name: Penn Jillette
bio: Penn Fraser Jillette is an American magician, juggler, comedian, musician, inventor, actor, and best-selling author known for his work with fellow magician Teller as half of the team Penn & Teller.

name: Bobby Jindal
bio: Piyush "Bobby" Jindal is an American politician who was the 55th Governor of Louisiana between 2008 and 2016, and previously served as a U.S. Congressman and as the vice chairman of the Republican Governors Association.

name: Ted Cruz
bio: Rafael Edward "Ted" Cruz is an American politician and attorney, who has served as the junior United States Senator from Texas since 2013. He was a candidate for the Republican nomination for President of the United States in the 2016 election.Cruz graduated from Princeton University, New Jersey, in 1992, and from Harvard Law School, Massachusetts, in 1995.

name: Rand Paul
bio: Randal Howard "Rand" Paul is an American politician and physician. Since 2011, Paul has served in the United States Senate as a member of the Republican Party representing Kentucky. He is the son of former U.S. Representative Ron Paul of Texas.

name: Rich Lowry
bio: Richard A. "Rich" Lowry is the editor of National Review, the American conservative magazine of news and opinion. He is also a syndicated columnist, author, and political commentator.

name: Rick Wilson
bio: Richard James "Rick" Wilson, Australian politician, is a Liberal Party of Australia member of the Australian House of Representatives since September 2013, representing the Division of O'Connor, Western Australia.

name: Rick Scott
bio: Richard Lynn "Rick" Scott is an American businessman and politician who has been the 45th Governor of Florida, since 2011. He is a member of the Republican Party of Florida.

name: Bob Vander Plaats
bio: Robert Lee "Bob" Vander Plaats is an American politician and political activist. He is currently the president and CEO of The Family Leader, a social conservative organization, and the National Co-Chair for Ted Cruz for President.

name: Robert Gates
bio: Robert Michael "Bob" Gates is an American statesman, scholar and university president who served as the 22nd United States Secretary of Defense from 2006 to 2011.

name: Woody Johnson
bio: Robert Wood "Woody" Johnson IV is an American businessman and philanthropist. He is a great-grandson of Robert Wood Johnson I, and the owner of the New York Jets of the National Football League.

name: Rodrigo Duterte
bio: Rodrigo "Rody" Roa Duterte, also known as Digong, is a Filipino politician and jurist who is the 16th and current President of the Philippines. He is the first Mindanaoan to hold the office, and the fourth of Visayan descent.

name: Ronda Rousey
bio: Ronda Jean Rousey is an American mixed martial artist, judoka, and actress. Rousey was the first U.S. woman to earn an Olympic medal in judo, which she won at the 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing.

name: Russell Moore
bio: Russell Moore and IIIrd Tyme Out is a bluegrass band formed in 1991 in Cumming, Georgia. Consisting of Russell Moore, Keith McKinnon, Justen Haynes, Wayne Benson and Blake Johnson, the band has released thirteen albums and two greatest hits collections since 1991.

name: Ruth Marcus
bio: Ruth Allyn Marcus is a Journalist who currently writes an op-ed column for The Washington Post. In March 2007, she was a finalist for the Pulitzer Prize for Commentary.

name: Ruth Bader Ginsburg
bio: Ruth Joan Bader Ginsburg is an Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States. Ginsburg was appointed by President Bill Clinton and took the oath of office on August 10, 1993.

name: Samuel L. Jackson
bio: Samuel Leroy Jackson is an American actor and film producer. He achieved prominence and critical acclaim in the early 1990s with films such as Jungle Fever, Patriot Games, Amos & Andrew, True Romance, Jurassic Park and his collaborations with director Quentin Tarantino including Pulp Fiction, Jackie Brown, Django Unchained, and The Hateful Eight.

name: Sam Liccardo
bio: Samuel Theodore "Sam" Liccardo is an American politician from California, currently serving as Mayor of San Jose. Liccardo was elected mayor in November 2014.

name: S.E. Cupp
bio: Sarah Elizabeth "S. E." Cupp is an American conservative political commentator and writer.She was a panelist on the CNN political debate show Crossfire, co-author of Why You're Wrong About the Right, with Brett Joshpe, and the sole author of Losing Our Religion: The Liberal Media's Attack on Christianity.

name: Scott Walker
bio: Scott Kevin Walker is the 45th and current Governor of Wisconsin. First elected governor in the 2010 Wisconsin general election, he survived a 2012 recall election and was reelected governor in the 2014 Wisconsin gubernatorial election.

name: Sopan Deb
bio: Sopan Deb is a political journalist for CBS News. He is also a stand up comic, NBA junkie and pianist.

name: Stephanie Rawlings-Blake
bio: Stephanie C. Rawlings-Blake is an American politician and the 49th and current mayor of Baltimore, Maryland. She is the second woman to hold the office.

name: Steve Rattner
bio: Steven Lawrence Rattner is an American financier who served as lead adviser to the Presidential Task Force on the Auto Industry in 2009 for the Obama administration.

name: Stuart Stevens
bio: Stuart Stevens is an American travel writer and political consultant. He was the cofounder of Washington, D.C. - based political media consultancy Stevens & Schriefer Group.

name: Tavis Smiley
bio: Tavis Smiley is an American talk show host, author, liberal political commentator, entrepreneur, advocate and philanthropist. Smiley was born in Gulfport, Mississippi, and grew up in Bunker Hill, Indiana.

name: Tom Ridge
bio: Thomas Joseph "Tom" Ridge is an American politician who served as the Assistant to the President for Homeland Security from 2001 to 2003, and the first United States Secretary of Homeland Security from 2003 to 2005.

name: Tim Kaine
bio: Timothy Michael "Tim" Kaine is an American attorney and politician serving as the junior United States Senator from Virginia. A Democrat, Kaine was elected to the Senate in 2012 and is the nominee of his party for Vice President of the United States in the 2016 election.

name: Tom Llamas
bio: Tom Llamas is an American news anchor and correspondent for ABC News. He is the Sunday anchor for ABC World News Tonight. He used to be the 5 pm anchor for WNBC's News 4 New York and a contributing correspondent for NBC News.

name: Tony Schwartz
bio: Tony Schwartz is an American journalist, business book author, professional speaker, and the ghostwriter and credited co-author of Trump: The Art of the Deal.

name: Mitt Romney
bio: Willard Mitt Romney, better known as Mitt Romney, is an American businessman and politician who served as the 70th Governor of Massachusetts from 2003 to 2007 and was the Republican Party's nominee for President of the United States in the 2012 election.

name: Bill Clinton
bio: William Jefferson Clinton is an American politician who served as the 42nd President of the United States from 1993 to 2001. Clinton was Governor of Arkansas from 1979 to 1981 and 1983 to 1992, and Arkansas Attorney General from 1977 to 1979.

name: Bill Kristol
bio: William Kristol is an American neoconservative political analyst and commentator. He is the founder and editor of the political magazine The Weekly Standard and a political commentator on several networks.

name: Willie Geist
bio: William Russell "Willie" Geist is an American television personality, journalist and humorist. He is co-anchor of MSNBC's Morning Joe and anchor of Sunday Today with Willie Geist. Geist also frequently serves as fill-in anchor on Today for Matt Lauer.

name: Tim O'Brien
bio: William Timothy "Tim" O'Brien is an American novelist best known for his work of fiction, The Things They Carried, a critically acclaimed collection of semi-autobiographical, interrelated short stories inspired by O'Brien's experiences in the Vietnam War.

name: Alicia Machado
bio: Yoseph Alicia Machado Fajardo known simply as Alicia Machado is a Venezuelan-born American actress, TV host, singer and beauty queen who was Miss Venezuela 1995 and then Miss Universe 1996.

name: Chris Stirewalt
bio: Chris Stirewalt joined Fox News Channel (FNC) in July of 2010 and serves as the networks digital politics editor based in Washington, D.C. Additionally, he writes a daily politics newsletter, Fox News First, and hosts Power Play" on FoxNews.com.

name: Clare O'Connor
bio: Clare O'Connor is a staff writer at Forbes Magazine covering women entrepreneurs and workplace equality.

name: Serge Kovaleski
bio: Serge F. Kovaleski is an investigative reporter at The New York Times.[1] He was born in Cape Town, South Africa, and graduated in 1984 from the College of William & Mary in Williamsburg, Virginia, having majored in philosophy.

name: Ben Schreckinger
bio: Ben Schreckinger covers national politics for Politico. In 2014, he lived in Boston and wrote on politics, economics, culture and their intersections for Slate, Newsweek, Politico Magazine, the Atlantic (digital), the Boston Globe, Boston Magazine, and the Financial Times, among others.

name: Jeff Horwitz
bio: Jeff Horwitz is a reporter writing about finance, banking, regulation and other business-related topics for the Associated Press in Washington.

name: Melinda Henneberger
bio: Melinda Henneberger is an Opinion Writer at USA Today. She also serves as a visiting fellow for the Catholic University of Americas Institute for Policy Research & Catholic Studies.

name: Lisa Belkin
bio: Lisa Belkin is the Huffington Posts Senior Columnist, reporting and opining on life, work and family.

name: Barbara Res
bio: Barbara Res is a real estate development and construction professional. She was the first female hard-hat boss to oversee an American skyscraper from start to finish.

name: John King
bio: John King is an American journalist. He is CNN's chief national correspondent, based in Washington, DC, and is anchor of its roundtable political discussion program Inside Politics.

name: Joe McQuaid
bio: Joe McQuaid is an American political reporter in New Hampshire for the Union Leader.

name: Frank VanderSloot
bio: Frank L. VanderSloot is an American entrepreneur, radio network owner, rancher, and political campaign financier. He is the founder and chief executive officer of Melaleuca, Inc.
